Take the backup of ETCD at the location /opt/etcd-backup.db on the controlplane node.
sudo ETCDCTL_API=3 etcdctl --cert /etc/kubernetes/pki/etcd/server.crt --key /etc/kubernetes/pki/etcd/server.key --cacert /etc/kubernetes/pki/etcd/ca.crt --endpoints=https://127.0.0.1:2379 snapshot save /opt/etcd-backup.db
This command uses the etcdctl command-line tool to create a snapshot of the ETCD data store. The --cert, --key, and --cacert flags are used to specify the paths to the SSL certificates and keys for ETCD authentication. The --endpoints flag specifies the endpoint for ETCD, which is set to https://127.0.0.1:2379 assuming the ETCD server is running on the control plane node itself. 
The snapshot save command saves the snapshot to the specified location /opt/etcd-backup.db with superuser (sudo) permissions.
